    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are looking kind of sickly. the leaves on the bottom are turning yellow and falling off. what do you think is going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves can be a bit of a mystery, but I'm happy to help you troubleshoot. It sounds like your tomato plants might be experiencing a bit of a \"garden goblin\" problem - a lack of nutrients, perhaps, or too much water causing root rot. The yellowing leaves on the lower parts of the plant are a classic sign of this. You might want to check your soil pH and adjust it if necessary, as tomatoes prefer a slightly acidic to neutral soil. \n\nAlso, make sure you're not overwatering - a well-draining potting mix can help prevent root rot. It's a bit like the old saying goes: \"A little water can be a good thing, but too much can be a garden goblin's delight!\"",
